caption: Great place to grab some food when in a hurry. The customer service is fast, prices are fair, excellent atmosphere. Keep up the good work
Like others have said, really great staff and great prices. Solid sushi option.

I go to this marvelous  place often because I enjoy the good air that is exist in this restaurant. The crew is awfuly welcoming and qualified. The service is exceptionally quick. Needless to say, the food you eat is first-rate. I ate there more than once and I was always happy. The price is fair. I highly suggest this place to to all.

We arrived at this spot for lunch. This place was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was a winning. the staff members were so friendly and we had a fantastic feeling. The food was just great. We had a great time and we will definitely return to this restaurant. We recommend this place to all.

I really wish they would open before 4pm. But they hands down have the best drunken noodles in DC. The staff is so friendly and goes out of their way every single time. Best customer service I've received in the city. Highly recommend.

Finest spot to eat something when in a hurry. Their customer service is speedy, pricing is fair, good ambience. I highly recommend this place
Great prices, extremely tasty. One of the better dragon rolls I’ve had. Delicious lycheetini.

I live one block away so I order from Toku a lot. Look out for their promotional discounts. The food is always tasty. A big plus is that whenever I've ordered, the food is usually ready by the time I walk over unless it's a busy evening, but then it is ready soon after arrival. Has friendly, courteous staff. I've ordered sushi, drunken noodles with chicken, chicken with red chili peppers, Thai basil chicken, soups. All tasty.
This spot is worth trying. They serve large portions for fair rates. Always well organized and with great vibes. Would recommend to others.

Very in enjoyable food. I got “fried squid”, but got breaded calamari half rings, which weren’t crispy, nor seasoned well. The spring rolls have no flavor — they are stuffed with some kind of cold noodle and one piece of shrimp and the sauce they come with is extra sweet to the point of being inedible. Asian food never disappointed me so

First time going there with my boyfriend. We'll give it a 2 star for the fact that the prices are really good and the sushi isnt THAT bad.. We ordered the squid tempura and there was a huge clump of black hair? Or fabric? We really weren't sure what it was. We also ordered the lobster rolls.. First 2 pieces were good but then the flavor got worse like spoiled lobster. I immediately felt so sick.. We had also ordered the sushi diner and there was only a couple pieces that were OK... Overall wouldnt come back. Both me and my boyfriend got sick

After 10 weeks of working from home, this place is our #1 go to , we started to order from them every week and a $100 order can yield 4 individual meals. They take your diet restrictions seriously and chef would call to confirm ingredient replacements.   Amazing food, amazing speed, amazing people. Best Sushi/Sashimi in town with the most reasonable price !

I told my friends about this place with my warmest recommendations. I visit this restaurant often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The meals are tasty and the team is attentive and cooperative. always when we visit this place we pass a lovely evening.  highly recommended.

For us to be on a quarantine they were very helpful and attentive to me and my friend who was craving sushi! They sushi was amazing and their fried rice is underrated, next time I go I’m gonna try their famous ramen !

The dining room smelled really weird, and the decor was kind of old, but the food was really  yummy. Came here around 5:30PM with my best friend. We ordered the Shrimp Tempura, Garlic Fried Rice and Pad Thai and the Dragon Roll. The rolls were HUGE, fresh and flavorful, the garlic fried rice was some of the best I'd ever had, and the Pad Thai was delicious. The Pad Thai more so on the sweeter side - my best friend asked if she could get it a little more spicy, but our waiter let us know that the sauce used was a sweeter sauce, and spice level could not be adjusted. Nonetheless, it was a solid place, service was "okay" but not horrible, but we'll definitely be back. They even have happy hour on sushi.

I had a great  in this restaurant. We liked the nice environment and the food. The staff were very affable. I am happy we ultimately managed to visit this place.

Great value for money. Pretty prompt service on a Sunday. Not too busy.  Really loved the tuna crunchy avocado cucumber salad (ask for a fork) and the $5 happy hour drinks. Chicken satay starter was ok. Coconut milk chicken soup was delicious and flavorful but the chicken it contained felt like a bit of an afterthought a bland chunks thrown in there. The sushi we had (an unagi roll and Mexican spicy tuna roll) was great. Tofu panang curry also good.  Our Sunday lunch for two comprised large chicken coconut soup, the tuna avocado appetizer, chicken satay appetizer, unagi sushi and spicy tuna sushi (6 pieces each), a tofu panang curry with rice which we shared, two HH cocktails, a mochi cream dessert and a fried banana dessert which came to about $75 plus tip.  I have to give these guys a shout out for offering reusable chopsticks. They are hard to work with but not as hard as a world without trees! If you need something with more grip, request a fork - judgment free.
The food is always well prepared and tasty, employees hands over fantastic customer service. I love how clean it is and character. Will visit here again.

Sushi rolled a little loose so it wanted to fall apart on the way into the mouth. Prompt response from owner, but I tend not to return items. Had a bad experience  elsewhere doing just that. Thanks. Overall decent.  But thought they should know for future.  Should be right the first time after all.
